-- Bonduelle Slumps After Saying 2010-11 Operating Profit to Drop on Harvests
-- B y   D a v i d   W h i t e h o u s e
-- 2010-10-05T07:04:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/bonduelle-slumps-after-saying-2010-11-operating-profit-to-drop-on-harvests.html
Bonduelle SCA shares fell in Paris
today after the producer of canned and frozen food said
operating profit will decline significantly in 2010-11, hurt by
difficult harvests and cost overruns.  The stock sank as much as 6.5 percent and was down 5.7
percent at 64.50 euros at 9:03 a.m. in Paris.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Whitehouse at 
 dwhitehouse1@bloomberg.net  